.TH TOTPGATE 1 2026-05-30 "totpgate" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
totpgate \- send a TOTP authorization packet
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B totpgate
\fB\-\-secret\fR \fIsecret\fR [\fIoptions\fR] \fIserver\fR[\fB:\fP\fIport\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBtotpgate\fR generates a TOTP token from the shared secret and sends it
as a UDP datagram to the daemon running on \fIserver\fR.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-secret\fR \fIsecret\fR
Shared secret. Base32 by default; prefix with \fBhex:\fR or \fBb64:\fR
for other encodings. (required)
.TP
\fB\-\-port\fR \fIport\fR
UDP port of the target daemon (default: 2222).
Ignored when \fIserver\fR includes a port (e.g. \fBserver:3333\fR).
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR
Display usage and exit.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
\fIserver\fR[\fB:\fP\fIport\fR]
IP address or hostname of the \fBtotpgated\fR daemon. When a port is
appended after a colon (e.g. \fB192.168.1.1:3333\fR) it overrides the
\fB\-\-port\fR option.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.P
\fBtotpgate\fR exits 0 on success, 1 on error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR totpgated (1)
